# Krishna Yajurveda - Taittiriya Samhita
# Kanda 1, Prapathaka 1
# The New and Full Moon Sacrifices - Opening

KRISHNA_YAJURVEDA_K1_P1 = {
    1: {
        "sanskrit": "अन्नाय त्वा बलाय त्वा । वायवः स्थोपायवः । देवस्त्वा सविता प्रणयतु श्रेष्ठतमाय कर्मणे । अजिता अस्मान् देवानां भागेनोप सदत सबलाः सपयसः सप्रजसो अनामया अरोगाः । मा वो जारो मा द्वायुरीशत । मा वो रुद्रस्य हेतिः परि वृक्षत । बह्वीर्या वः स्थ नाभिमिदं जनस्य गोपायत । गोपाय यजमानस्य पशून् ॥",
        "meaning": "For food thee, for strength thee! Ye are winds, ye are approachers. Let the god Savitr impel you to the most excellent offering. O invincible ones, swell with the share for the gods, full of strength, of milk, rich in offspring, free from sickness, from disease. Let no thief, no evil worker, have control over you. Let Rudra's dart avoid you. Abide ye, numerous, with this lord of cattle. Do thou protect the cattle of the sacrificer.",
        "example": "Food and strength are offered first. Your intention is the offering. One clear intention set today. That intention is food for your spirit and strength for your action. Not separate. Both."
    },
    2: {
        "sanskrit": "यज्ञस्य घासोऽसि । प्रदह्य रक्षः प्रदह्यारातीः । वेदिरसि बर्हिषः प्रियधामा मानुषी स्वधया संभृता । अग्रेण मनसा स्तृणन्ति तां देवेभ्यो बर्हि हर्यतं नि सीद । देवसू रसि । वर्षक्रियासि । बर्हिर्देवि प्रति त्वा भूर्नि तिष्ठामि मा त्वोपस्पृशं मा त्वोपस्पृशं छिनदं मा ते च्छित्सि । शतेन प्राची शतेनोदीची शतेन व्यायता शतिनीर्या यूयं स्थ तासां वः शतिनीनां शतं शतमुप सदे । पृथिव्याः संस्पृशः पाहि । शोभमाना सं भरामि त्वा । अदित्यै रास्नासीन्द्राण्या उपानहौ । पूषा ते ग्रन्थिं ग्रन्थातामुत्सं ग्रन्थिं ग्रन्थेय । इन्द्रस्य बाहुभ्यामुत्थितोऽस्मि बृहस्पतेर्मूर्ध्ना गृहीतोस्मि । विश्वं विष्णुः प्र चर त्वं वित्तं देवेषु गच्छतम् ॥",
        "meaning": "Thou art the substance of the sacrifice. The Raksas is burned up, the evil spirits are burned up. The Vedi hath come to the sacrificial straw, Made by Manu, fashioned with the Svadha call. The sages fetch it from in front, The delightful straw for the gods to sit on here. Thou art impelled by the gods. Thou art made to grow by the rains. O divine straw, let me not hit thee either across or along, Let me hit thy joints, Let me come to no harm in cutting thee. O divine straw, rise with a hundred shoots, Let us rise with a thousand shoots. Guard from the contact of earth. I gather thee with good gathering. Thou art the girdle of Aditi, the cord of Indrani. Let Pusan tie a knot for thee, that knot shall mount me. I hold thee up with the arms of Indra, I seize thee with the head of Brhaspati. Fare along the wide atmosphere. Thou art going to the gods.",
        "example": "The Raksas is your inner obstruction. One excuse you make repeatedly. Name it today. That naming is the burning. Not by force. By naming. Aditi's girdle is the boundary that protects your true self from false obligations. One boundary set today. That boundary is the knot Pusan ties."
    },
    3: {
        "sanskrit": "पवित्रस्थो दैव्या कर्मणे देवयज्यायै । मातरिश्वनो घर्मोऽसि । द्यौरसि पृथिव्यसि । विश्वधाया विश्वतोधाया अस्यै । ध्रुवासीदं त्वा च्यावयानि । वसूनां पवित्रं शतधारं वसूनां सहस्रधारम् । इष्टः स्तोको न्युप्तो बिन्दुः । अग्नये गायत्राय छागलो अग्नेरग्निष्ठो द्युभक्ततमो देवानां देवतमः । अग्ने वैश्वानरोदित सोमं यज्ञं वह देवेभ्यः । ऊर्जो नपात् प्रति त्वं देवश्रूः सोम याम्नो देवानां देवतमः । आयुषा रश्मीन् प्रति बध्नाति । इन्द्रियेण तेजसा ब्रह्मवर्चसेन । त्वष्टा रूपाणि प्रति मुञ्चतां नः । इन्द्रः सोमं पिबतु प्रजापतिर्हिनोतु । प्रजापते न त्वदेतान्यन्यो विश्वा जातानि परि ता बभूव । यत्कामास्ते जुहुमस्तन्नो अस्तु वयं स्याम पतयो रयीणाम् ॥",
        "meaning": "Be ye pure for the divine rite, the sacrifice to the gods. Thou art the cauldron of Matarisvan. Thou art the heaven, thou art the earth. Thou art the all-supporting with the highest support. Be firm, waver not. Thou art the strainer of the Vasus, of a hundred streams, thou art that of the Vasus, of a thousand streams. The spot has been offered, the drop has been offered. To Agni, to the mighty firmament! Hail to sky and earth! This is she of all life, this is the all-encompassing, this is the all-doing. Be ye united, that follow holy orders, Ye that wave and are fullest of sweetness, Delightful for the gaining of wealth. With Soma I curdle thee, curds for Indra. O Visnu, guard the offering.",
        "example": "The strainer of a hundred streams is your attention. One thought filtered through awareness today. Not reacted. Filtered. That filtering is the pure rite. Visnu guards the offering when you act with presence, not when you act with distraction. Guard your own offering by being present."
    },
    4: {
        "sanskrit": "कर्मणे वां देवेभ्यो मयोभूवम् । कर्म क्रियमाणमसि । प्रदह्य रक्षः प्रदह्यारातीः । योकोसि । अररिन्द्र द्विषन्तं यः प्रतिधरं जिघांसति द्विषन्तं यो अस्मान् प्रतिधरं जिघांसति । देवानां गातुवित्तमो रेवतीतमः सुविततमो भवतो युञ्जानतमो होतृभ्य आह्वरतमो बर्हिर्देवसदनं ध्रुवमसि । उपरवः स्थ परिवयः स्थ । ध्रुवमसि । मा च्यविष्ठा निषदनमसि निषदनं मा व्यथिष्ठाः । मित्रस्य त्वा चक्षुषा प्रतीक्षे । मा भैष्म मा संविक्था मा त्वा हिंसिषम् । अन्तरिक्षस्य वाते जनित्वरी । देव सवितः प्रसुव यज्ञं प्रसुव यज्ञपतिं भगाय । देवस्य त्वा सवितुः प्रसवेऽश्विनोर्बाहुभ्यां पूष्णो हस्ताभ्याम् अग्नये जुष्टं गृह्णामि अग्नीषोमाभ्याम् । देवानां य इदमिदमस्माकं च । पुष्ट्यै त्वा न पाप्मने । ज्योतिर्वैश्वानरं प्रजाभ्यो देवेभ्यः कल्पताम् । स्वर्गाय लोकाय संवसन्तौ दिवं च पृथिवीं चानु वित्त संचरन्तौ । अदित्याः सदोन्यक्रान्न् अग्ने यज्ञं पाहि ॥",
        "meaning": "For the rite you two, for the gods may I be strong. Thee for accomplishment! The Raksas is burnt up, the evil spirits are burnt up. Thou art the yoke. Injure him who injures us, injure him whom we injure. Thou art of gods the most firmly jointed, the most richly filled, the most agreeable, the best of carriers, the best caller of the gods. Thou art the oblation-holder that wavers not. Be firm, waver not. I gaze on thee with the eye of Mitra. Be not afraid, be not troubled, let me harm thee not. (Be thou) wide open to the wind. On the impulse of the god Savitr, with the arms of the Asvins, with the hands of Pusan, I offer thee dear to Agni, to Agni and Soma. This of the gods, this of us too. For prosperity thee, not for misfortune. May I behold the light, the radiance for all men. May they that have doors stand firm in heaven and earth. Fare along the wide atmosphere. I place thee in the lap of Aditi. O Agni, guard the offering.",
        "example": "The yoke connects your intention to action. One intention acted today. That action is the yoke. Mitra's eye is friendship with yourself. Gaze at your effort with kindness, not criticism. Not harsh. Kind. The lap of Aditi is infinite space where all actions rest. Place your effort there without attachment to outcome. Not grasping. Offering."
    },
    5: {
        "sanskrit": "देवस्त्वा सविता पुनातु वसोः पवित्रेण शश्वतीभिस्तनूभिर्गायत्रेण च्छन्दसाग्नेः साम्ना ब्रह्मणा देवा यज्ञं नयन्तु । अपो देवीरग्रेगुवो अग्रेगावो अग्रे यज्ञियाः शिवा नः शिवया विश्पतिं धत्त यज्ञं पुरस्ताद्यज्ञियं नयत । इन्द्रस्त्वा वृत्राय वृणीत त्वमिन्द्राय वृत्राय वृणीष्व । स्थोवानोसि । अग्नये जुष्टं जुहोम्यग्नीषोमाभ्याम् । पवित्रस्थो दैव्या कर्मणे देवयज्यायै । अवधूतं रक्षोऽवधूता अरातयः । अदित्यै देवानां जनित्रे जरायु । पृथिवी त्वा पर्यगृह्णात् पृथिवी त्वा परिगृह्णातु मा त्वा परि वर्ग्म । अदित्यै देवानां जनित्रे जरायु । अग्नेर्वर्मासि वैश्वानरस्य पुरीषवती प्रपदने धारया वाचं वदता वदत मधु । श्लोकं कृणुत पुण्यं संग्रामेषु वनामहे । प्रजापतेस्त्वा वर्ष्मन्नध्यातिष्ठिपम् । स्वदितं ते ब्रह्मणा । निरस्तः शरुः सविता प्रणयन् कलशान् गृभाय सुवर्गाय लोकाय । मा भूदीशानः प्रथमो यस्य वशे बृहस्पतिः पुनर्याम्ने सं भरामि ॥",
        "meaning": "Let the god Savitr purify you, with a filter that has no flaw, with the rays of the bright sun. Ye divine waters, that go in front and first purify, forward lead this sacrifice, place in front the lord of the sacrifice. You Indra chose for the contest with Vrtra, ye chose Indra for the contest with Vrtra. Ye are sprinkled. I sprinkle you agreeable to Agni, to Agni and Soma. Be ye pure for the divine rite, for the sacrifice to the gods. The Raksas is shaken off, the evil spirits are shaken off. Thou art the skin of Aditi, may the earth recognize thee. Thou art the plank of wood, may the skin of Aditi recognize thee. Thou art the body of Agni, loosener of speech. I grasp thee for the joy of the gods. Thou art the stone of wood. Do thou with good labour elaborate this offering for the gods. Utter food, utter strength; Make ye glorious sounds. May we be victorious in contest. Thou art increased by the rain. May that which is increased by the rain recognize thee. The Raksas is cleared away, the evil spirits are cleared away. Thou art the share of the Raksases. Let the wind separate you. Let the god Savitr of golden hands, seize you.",
        "example": "The filter with no flaw is your clear intention. One motive purified of self-deception. That purification is Savitr's ray. The contest with Vrtra is your battle with inner blockage. One blockage faced today, not avoided. That facing is Indra's choice. Not avoiding. Facing. Victory is not destroying the blockage. Seeing it clearly."
    },
    6: {
        "sanskrit": "अवधूतं रक्षोऽवधूता अरातयः । अदित्यै देवानां जनित्रे जरायु । पृथिवी त्वा पर्यगृह्णात् पृथिवी त्वा परिगृह्णातु मा त्वा परि वर्ग्म । अदित्यै देवानां जनित्रे जरायु । दिवस्कन्दः प्रति दिवस्कन्दं गृह्णामि प्रति त्वा दिवस्कन्दः प्रति गृह्णातु । अदित्यै देवानां जनित्रे जरायु । अश्मन्नसि कुतम्मुरस्त्वमसि कुतम्मुर्वित्त्वैतत् । देवस्य त्वा सवितुः प्रसवेऽश्विनोर्बाहुभ्यां पूष्णो हस्ताभ्याम् उत्क्षिपामि । प्राणाय त्वा, अपानाय त्वा, व्यानाय त्वोत्क्षिपामि । अग्नेर्भस्मासि वैश्वानरस्य । दीर्घमायुर्यजमानाय कृणुहि । देवस्त्वा सविता हिरण्यपाणिः प्रति गृह्णातु ॥",
        "meaning": "The Raksas is shaken off, the evil spirits are shaken off. Thou art the skin of Aditi, may the earth recognize thee. Thou art the supporter of the sky, may the skin of Aditi recognize thee. Thou art a bowl of rock, may the supporter of the sky recognize thee. Thou art a bowl made of the rock, may the rock recognize thee. On the impulse of the god Savitr, with the arms of the Asvins, with the hands of Pusan, I pour thee out. Thou art stimulating, stimulate the gods. For expiration thee, for inspiration thee, for through-breathing thee (I pound). May I extend for long the life (of the sacrificer). Let the god Savitr, of golden hands, seize you.",
        "example": "Expiration and inspiration are your breath. One breath with full awareness today. That breath extends your life not in years but in presence. The bowl of rock is your body made of stable elements. One action that honors your body's limits. Not overextending. Respecting. Savitr of golden hands seizes you when you act with golden intention — pure, not mixed."
    },
    7: {
        "sanskrit": "प्रौग्भ्य आ ते उप त्वा । अग्ने यद्द्याव अपरिच्छिन्नमुग्र प्रचेतस्तं त्वा दूतं कृण्वते द्विबर्हसं पर्यग्ने वैश्वानर दह प्रतीचो ये अस्मभ्यं शपथं कृण्वते प्रति तान् विधेम । ध्रुवासि । पृथिवी ध्रुवा । आयुर्ध्रुवा । प्रजाध्रुवा । एतं यजमानं ध्रुवेण ध्रुवमकम् । ध्रुवासि । अन्तरिक्षं ध्रुवम् । प्राणोध्रुवः । अपानोध्रुवः । एतं यजमानं ध्रुवेण ध्रुवमकम् । ध्रुवासि । द्यौर्ध्रुवा । चक्षुर्ध्रुवम् । श्रोत्रं ध्रुवम् । एतं यजमानं ध्रुवेण ध्रुवमकम् । ध्रुवासि । दिशोध्रुवाः । आत्मा ध्रुवः । प्रजाध्रुवा । एतं यजमानं ध्रुवेण ध्रुवमकम् । संयत्ता अस्मै यजमानाय प्रजां पशून् विशं वर्चो दधातन । भृगूणामङ्गिरसां तपसा तप्यध्वम् । कपालानि कवये विद्मनायुनाजान् पूष्णा सङ्गृभीता इन्द्रवायू वि मुञ्चतम् ॥",
        "meaning": "Bold art thou, support our prayer. O Agni, drive off the fire that eats raw flesh, send away the corpse-eating one, bring hither the fire that sacrifices to the gods. The Raksas is burnt, the evil spirits are burnt. Thou art firm; make firm the earth, make life firm, make offspring firm, make his followers subordinate to this sacrificer. Thou art a supporter, make firm the atmosphere, make expiration firm, make inspiration firm, make his fellows subordinate to this sacrificer. Thou art supporting, make the heaven firm, make the eye firm, make the ear firm, make his fellows, &c. Thou art a support, make the quarters firm, make the organ firm, make offspring firm, make his fellows, &c. Ye are gatherers, bring offspring to this sacrificer, wealth to him, make his fellows, &c. Be ye heated with the heat of the Bhrgus and the Angirases. The potsherds which wise men collect for the cauldron, these are in Pusan's guardianship. Let Indra and Vayu set them free.",
        "example": "The fire that eats raw flesh is your unprocessed anger. One anger felt fully without acting from it. That feeling transforms raw flesh into cooked offering. Not suppression. Cooking. Bhrgus and Angirases are the ancestors of wisdom. Their heat is the fire of past lessons. One past lesson applied today. That application heats the potsherds of your effort. Indra and Vayu set them free when you act, not when you only think."
    },
    8: {
        "sanskrit": "श्रीणामि । आपो देवीर्देवां अप इमास्ताः सं श्रीणामि । ओषधीभिरोषधीः सं श्रीणामि । जरदष्टीर्जरदष्टीः सं श्रीणामि । सुप्रजसस्त्वा वयं सं श्रीणामि । अग्नये त्वाग्नीषोमाभ्याम् । मखस्य शिरोऽसि । सर्वायुर्घर्मोऽसि । वित्तं विस्तारि यजमानाय । अजस्रमा रभस्व । विक्षरद्वित्तं यजमानाय । प्रजनिषीमहि सुप्रजसः सं श्रीणामि । प्रत्यूढं रक्षः प्रत्यूढा अरातयः । विश्वकर्मा त्वा सविता सं मार्ष्टु । माभिबुधः शरीरम् । अग्ने यज्ञं पाहि । युजे रथं गविष्ठिरो वहद्वामग्निरभवत् । एकतायै स्वाहा द्वितायै स्वाहा त्रितायै स्वाहा ॥",
        "meaning": "I pour together. The waters have joined with the waters, the plants with sap. Join ye rich ones with the moving ones, sweet ones with the sweet. From the waters ye are born, be united with the waters. For generation I unite thee. For Agni thee, for Agni and Soma. Thou art the head of Makha. Thou art the cauldron that contains all life. Be extended wide, let the lord of the sacrifice be extended wide. Grasp the skin. The Raksas is obstructed, the evil spirits are obstructed. Let the god Savitr make thee ready on the highest firmament. May Agni burn not too much thy body. O Agni, guard the offering. Be united with our prayer. Hail to Ekata, hail to Dvita, hail to Trita.",
        "example": "Waters joining with waters is your conscious mind joining your unconscious. One dream remembered today. Not interpreted. Remembered. That remembering is the joining. Ekata (Oneness), Dvita (Duality), Trita (Threefold) are the stages of creation. One action that moves from oneness (intention) through duality (choice) to threefold (thought, word, deed aligned). That action is the hail. Not words. Action."
    },
    9: {
        "sanskrit": "गृह्णामि ते । इन्द्रस्य बाहुरसि दक्षिणः सहस्रभृष्टिः शततेजाः । स वायुरसि वायुसखा श्येनाय श्येन पक्षा भूत्वा स्वरितः । पृथिवि देवयजन्योषधीभ्यस्त्वा गृह्णामि मा ते रिषम् । अप क्रमादरारुः । व्रजं गच्छ गोस्थानम् । दिवे त्वा वर्षाय । देव सवितः शतेन पाशैरव ते हृदय आ वया जहि प्राच्या दिशो यो अस्मान् द्वेष्टि यं वयं द्विष्मस्तमतो जहि । अप क्रमादरारुः पृथिव्याः संवेशनाद् व्रजं गच्छ गोस्थानम् । दिवे त्वा वर्षाय । देव सवितः शतेन पाशैरव ते हृदय आ वया जहि प्राच्या दिशो यो अस्मान् द्वेष्टि यं वयं द्विष्मस्तमतो जहि । अप क्रमादरारुः पृथिव्या अदेवयजनाद् व्रजं गच्छ गोस्थानम् । दिवे त्वा वर्षाय । देव सवितः शतेन पाशैरव ते हृदय आ वया जहि प्राच्या दिशो यो अस्मान् द्वेष्टि यं वयं द्विष्मस्तमतो जहि । मा तेऽरारुर्दिवमाक्रमत् । गायत्रेण त्वा छन्दसा गृह्णातु त्वष्टा गायत्रेण त्वा छन्दसा गृह्णातु । देव सवितः प्रसुव यज्ञं प्रसुव यज्ञपतिं भगाय । धर्मासि सुधर्मा यशो धर्मणि त्वा । धर्तासि सुधर्ता यशो धरणे त्वा । पृथुरसि वीरुधां पतिर्बृहदुक्षे विश्वारूपा आभरन्ती पृथिवीमुप जीविकाम् । अररुर्ध्राजत प्रागात् सूर्यो ज्योतिषा पुनः ॥",
        "meaning": "I grasp (thee). Thou art Indra's right arm with a thousand spikes, a hundred edges. Thou art the wind of sharp edge. O earth whereon sacrifice is offered to the gods, let me harm not the root of thy plant. Araru is smitten away from the earth. Go to the fold where the cattle are. May heaven rain for thee. O god Savitr, bind thou in the furthest distance with a hundred fetters him who hateth us and whom we hate, thence let him not free. Araru is smitten away from the earth, the place of sacrifice. Go to the fold where the cattle are. May heaven rain for thee. O god Savitr, &c. Araru is smitten away from the earth, he that sacrifices not to the gods. Go to the fold where the cattle are. May heaven rain for thee. O god Savitr, &c. Let not Araru mount the sky for thee. Let the Vasus grasp thee with the Gayatri metre, let the Rudras grasp thee with the Tristubh metre, let the Adityas grasp thee with the Jagati metre. On the impulse of the god Savitr wise ones perform the rite. Thou art the right, thou art the seat of right, thou art the glory of right. Thou art the holder, thou art the self-holder. Thou art broad, and wealthy art thou. Before the cruel foe slips away, O glorious one, Taking up the earth, with plenteous drops, The earth which they place in the moon by their offerings, Which wise men use to guide them in the sacrifice.",
        "example": "Indra's arm with a thousand spikes is your determination. One task done with full focus. That focus is the thousand spikes piercing through distraction. Not many tasks. One. Araru is the energy of non-sacrifice — action without intention. One action done with pure intention today. That intention smites Araru. Not by fighting. By acting differently. The Vasus (earthly powers), Rudras (stormy powers), Adityas (cosmic powers) grasp you when your action serves all levels — physical, emotional, and spiritual. Not serving one. Serving all."
    },
    10: {
        "sanskrit": "प्रदह्य रक्षः प्रदह्यारातीः । अग्ने यत्ते तेजस्तेन त्वा सं दहामि त्रिवृता गायत्रेण तप्तं तप्तं घर्ममवतप्तम् । मा सं सृक्ष्महि पशूनां गोस्थानम् । अहं त्वा सं सृजामि य ओजिष्ठो अभिभूतिः । वाचं वाचं प्राणं प्राणं चक्षुश्चक्षुः श्रोत्रं श्रोत्रं प्रजां प्रजननमहं निर्णेज्मि । अग्निं याचे प्रजां याचे सुप्रजास्त्वं याचे। अग्ने सुप्रजा इह स्याम सुभगा अर्यमन्वते। विश्वे देवासो अदिते सुप्रजस्त्वं नयत। विमोचनी संज्ञानी स्वाहा । आयुषा तेजसा ब्रह्मवर्चसेन प्रजया पशुभिः पुनरुप सदे । आयुष्मान् यजमानो दीर्घमायुरस्तु प्रजया पशुभिः पुनरुप सदे । जीवं रुद्रस्य दण्डमप एहि पुनर्जीवं प्रति तिष्ठ । विश्वे देवा अनु त्वा दधिरे सं प्रियेण धाम्ना प्रियेण चक्षुषा प्रियया प्रतिष्ठया ॥",
        "meaning": "The Raksas is burnt up, the evil spirits are burnt up. With Agni's keenest flame I burn you. May I not brush the place of the cattle, I brush thee that art strong and overcomest foes. Speech, breath, eye, ear, offspring, the organ of generation may I not brush, I brush thee that art strong and overcomest foes. Beseeching favour, offspring, prosperity, in devotion to Agni, I gird my body for good action. With fair offspring, with noble husbands, We are come to thee, O Agni, to thee that deceivest the foe, The undeceivable, we that are not deceived. I loosen this bond of Varuna, Which Savitr the kindly hath bound, And in the birthplace of the creator, in the place of good action, I make it pleasant for me with my husband. With life, with offspring, O Agni, with splendour again, As wife with my husband I am united. United be my spirit with my body.",
        "example": "Agni's keenest flame is your most focused attention. One moment of pure focus today. That focus burns the Raksas of distraction. Not by force. By presence. Varuna's bond is the attachment to outcomes. One action done without attachment to result. That action loosens the bond. Not by indifference. By offering. United be my spirit with my body means one action where you are fully present, not split between doing and thinking. Not split. Whole. This completes Kanda 1, Prapathaka 1."
    }
}
