KRISHNA_YAJURVEDA_K1_P5 = {
    1: {
        "sanskrit": "दक्षिणा वै यज्ञस्य प्रतिष्ठा । यद्दक्षिणा न दद्याद्यज्ञो विशीर्येत । तस्माद्दक्षिणा देयाः । अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्नेरेव तन्मुखं प्रीणाति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रियस्यैव तद्रूपं प्रीणाति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सवितुरेव तद्रूपं प्रीणाति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । ब्रह्मण एव तद्रूपं प्रीणाति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णोरेव तद्रूपं प्रीणाति ।",
        "meaning": "The sacrificial fees are the foundation of the sacrifice. If he should not give fees, the sacrifice would collapse. Therefore fees should be given. He gives a gold coin to Agni; thereby he gratifies the mouth of Agni. He gives a gold coin to Indra; thereby he gratifies the form of Indra's power. He gives a gold coin to Savitr; thereby he gratifies the form of Savitr. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati; thereby he gratifies the form of Brahman. He gives a gold coin to Visnu; thereby he gratifies the form of Visnu.",
        "example": "Sacrificial fees are what you give back after receiving. One act of gratitude today for something you have received. Not as transaction. As recognition. That act is the foundation. Not receiving without giving. The gold coin is not money — it is attention. One moment of attention given back to the source of a gift. A thank you. Acknowledgment. That attention gratifies the gods — your higher self recognizes itself in the cycle of giving and receiving."
    },
    2: {
        "sanskrit": "अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्निर्वै देवानामवमः । अग्निमेव तदवमं करोति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रो वै देवानां मध्यमः । इन्द्रमेव तन्मध्यमं करोति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सविता वै देवानां प्रसविता । सवितारमेव तत्प्रसवितारं करोति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतिर्वै देवानां ब्रह्मा । बृहस्पतिमेव तद्ब्रह्माणं करोति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णुर्वै देवानां परमः । विष्णुमेव तत्परमं करोति ।",
        "meaning": "He gives a gold coin to Agni; Agni is the lowest of the gods; thus he makes him the lowest. He gives a gold coin to Indra; Indra is the middle of the gods; thus he makes him the middle. He gives a gold coin to Savitr; Savitr is the impeller of the gods; thus he makes him the impeller. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati; Brhaspati is the Brahman of the gods; thus he makes him the Brahman. He gives a gold coin to Visnu; Visnu is the highest of the gods; thus he makes him the highest.",
        "example": "The hierarchy of gods is not about superiority. It is about function. Agni (lowest) is your immediate action. Indra (middle) is your sustained courage. Savitr (impeller) is your awakening. Brhaspati (Brahman) is your wisdom. Visnu (highest) is your preserving vision. One action that touches all five levels. Not just immediate. Immediate, sustained, awakened, wise, preserving. That action gives gold to all gods. Not one at a time. One action contains all."
    },
    3: {
        "sanskrit": "अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्नेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदग्निं समर्धयति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रस्य वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदिन्द्रं समर्धयति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सवितुर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तत्सवितारं समर्धयति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्बृहस्पतिं समर्धयति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णोर्वै रуक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्विष्णुं समर्धयति ।",
        "meaning": "He gives a gold coin to Agni. The gold coin is the form of Agni; by the form he perfects Agni. He gives a gold coin to Indra. The gold coin is the form of Indra; by the form he perfects Indra. He gives a gold coin to Savitr. The gold coin is the form of Savitr; by the form he perfects Savitr. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati. The gold coin is the form of Brhaspati; by the form he perfects Brhaspati. He gives a gold coin to Visnu. The gold coin is the form of Visnu; by the form he perfects Visnu.",
        "example": "The gold coin is your intention. One clear intention set today. That intention is the form of the god — not the physical form, but the essential nature. Intention to act (Agni), intention to persevere (Indra), intention to awaken (Savitr), intention to speak wisely (Brhaspati), intention to preserve (Visnu). One intention that contains all five. That intention perfects the gods within you. Not by worship. By intention."
    },
    4: {
        "sanskrit": "एकरूपं वा एतद्यद्रुक्मः । एकरूपेण वै देवा देवताः समारोहयन् । तद्यद्रुक्मं ददाति देवता एव तत्समारोहयति । अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्नेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदग्निं समर्धयति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रस्य वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदिन्द्रं समर्धयति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सवितुर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तत्सवितारं समर्धयति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्बृहस्पतिं समर्धयति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णोर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्विष्णुं समर्धयति ।",
        "meaning": "The gold coin is one-formed. With the one-formed the gods raised up the divinities. When he gives a gold coin, he raises up the divinities. He gives a gold coin to Agni. The gold coin is the form of Agni; by the form he perfects Agni. He gives a gold coin to Indra. The gold coin is the form of Indra; by the form he perfects Indra. He gives a gold coin to Savitr. The gold coin is the form of Savitr; by the form he perfects Savitr. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati. The gold coin is the form of Brhaspati; by the form he perfects Brhaspati. He gives a gold coin to Visnu. The gold coin is the form of Visnu; by the form he perfects Visnu.",
        "example": "One-formed means your intention is singular, not divided. One clear intention today, not many scattered intentions. That singular intention raises up the divinities — your inner powers are not separate when your intention is one. Not many gods fighting. One intention, one action. That action contains all forms. Not five coins. One coin. One intention."
    },
    5: {
        "sanskrit": "अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्निर्वै देवानामवमः । अग्निं तदवमं करोति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रो वै देवानां मध्यमः । इन्द्रं तन्मध्यमं करोति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सविता वै देवानां प्रसविता । सवितारं तत्प्रसवितारं करोति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतिर्वै देवानां ब्रह्मा । बृहस्पतिं तद्ब्रह्माणं करोति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णुर्वै देवानां परमः । विष्णुं तत्परमं करोति ।",
        "meaning": "He gives a gold coin to Agni; Agni is the lowest of the gods; thus he makes him the lowest. He gives a gold coin to Indra; Indra is the middle of the gods; thus he makes him the middle. He gives a gold coin to Savitr; Savitr is the impeller of the gods; thus he makes him the impeller. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati; Brhaspati is the Brahman of the gods; thus he makes him the Brahman. He gives a gold coin to Visnu; Visnu is the highest of the gods; thus he makes him the highest.",
        "example": "Making the gods lowest, middle, impeller, Brahman, highest is not hierarchy. It is ordering. One action that moves from immediate (lowest) to highest (vision). Not jumping. Moving. First act (Agni), then sustain (Indra), then awaken (Savitr), then speak wisdom (Brhaspati), then preserve the whole (Visnu). One action that follows this order. Not random. Ordered. That order makes the gods function together, not against each other."
    },
    6: {
        "sanskrit": "अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्निर्वै देवानामवमः । अग्निमेव तदवमं करोति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रो वै देवानां मध्यमः । इन्द्रमेव तन्मध्यमं करोति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सविता वै देवानां प्रसविता । सवितारमेव तत्प्रसवितारं करोति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतिर्वै देवानां ब्रह्मा । बृहस्पतिमेव तद्ब्रह्माणं करोति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णुर्वै देवानां परमः । विष्णुमेव तत्परमं करोति ।",
        "meaning": "He gives a gold coin to Agni; Agni is the lowest of the gods; thus he makes him the lowest. He gives a gold coin to Indra; Indra is the middle of the gods; thus he makes him the middle. He gives a gold coin to Savitr; Savitr is the impeller of the gods; thus he makes him the impeller. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati; Brhaspati is the Brahman of the gods; thus he makes him the Brahman. He gives a gold coin to Visnu; Visnu is the highest of the gods; thus he makes him the highest.",
        "example": "Repetition for emphasis. Each giving is an act of recognition. One act of recognition today for each aspect of your will: the spark (Agni), the courage (Indra), the awakening (Savitr), the wisdom (Brhaspati), the vision (Visnu). Not one at a time. One action that recognizes all five. That recognition makes them function. Not by force. By recognition."
    },
    7: {
        "sanskrit": "अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्नेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदग्निं समर्धयति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रस्य वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदिन्द्रं समर्धयति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सवितुर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तत्सवितारं समर्धयति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्बृहस्पतिं समर्धयति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णोर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्विष्णुं समर्धयति ।",
        "meaning": "He gives a gold coin to Agni. The gold coin is the form of Agni; by the form he perfects Agni. He gives a gold coin to Indra. The gold coin is the form of Indra; by the form he perfects Indra. He gives a gold coin to Savitr. The gold coin is the form of Savitr; by the form he perfects Savitr. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati. The gold coin is the form of Brhaspati; by the form he perfects Brhaspati. He gives a gold coin to Visnu. The gold coin is the form of Visnu; by the form he perfects Visnu.",
        "example": "Perfection is not flawlessness. It is completeness. One intention that is complete — not partial, not hesitant. That complete intention perfects the god within you. Not by eliminating imperfection. By including all parts. The form is the shape of your intention. One clear shape. Not vague. That shaped intention is the gold coin. It perfects because it is complete, not because it is flawless."
    },
    8: {
        "sanskrit": "एकरूपं वा एतद्यद्रुक्मः । एकरूपेण वै देवा देवताः समारोहयन् । तद्यद्रुक्मं ददाति देवता एव तत्समारोहयति । अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्नेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदग्निं समर्धयति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रस्य वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदिन्द्रं समर्धयति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सवितुर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तत्सवितारं समर्धयति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्बृहस्पतिं समर्धयति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णोर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्विष्णुं समर्धयति ।",
        "meaning": "The gold coin is one-formed. With the one-formed the gods raised up the divinities. When he gives a gold coin, he raises up the divinities. He gives a gold coin to Agni. The gold coin is the form of Agni; by the form he perfects Agni. He gives a gold coin to Indra. The gold coin is the form of Indra; by the form he perfects Indra. He gives a gold coin to Savitr. The gold coin is the form of Savitr; by the form he perfects Savitr. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati. The gold coin is the form of Brhaspati; by the form he perfects Brhaspati. He gives a gold coin to Visnu. The gold coin is the form of Visnu; by the form he perfects Visnu.",
        "example": "Raising up the divinities means your inner powers become active, not dormant. One action today that activates your will (Agni), your courage (Indra), your awakening (Savitr), your wisdom (Brhaspati), your vision (Visnu). Not one at a time. One action activates all. How? By being fully present. Presence activates all powers. Not by doing five things. By doing one thing with full presence."
    },
    9: {
        "sanskrit": "दक्षिणा वै यज्ञस्य प्रतिष्ठा । यद्दक्षिणा न दद्याद्यज्ञो विशीर्येत । तस्माद्दक्षिणा देयाः । अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्नेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदग्निं समर्धयति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रस्य वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदिन्द्रं समर्धयति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सवितुर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तत्सवितारं समर्धयति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्बृहस्पतिं समर्धयति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णोर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्विष्णुं समर्धयति ।",
        "meaning": "The sacrificial fees are the foundation of the sacrifice. If he should not give fees, the sacrifice would collapse. Therefore fees should be given. He gives a gold coin to Agni. The gold coin is the form of Agni; by the form he perfects Agni. He gives a gold coin to Indra. The gold coin is the form of Indra; by the form he perfects Indra. He gives a gold coin to Savitr. The gold coin is the form of Savitr; by the form he perfects Savitr. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati. The gold coin is the form of Brhaspati; by the form he perfects Brhaspati. He gives a gold coin to Visnu. The gold coin is the form of Visnu; by the form he perfects Visnu.",
        "example": "The sacrifice is your action. The fees are what you give back. One act of giving back after receiving. A thank you. Acknowledgment. That acknowledgment is the foundation. Without it, the action collapses into transaction. Not sacrifice. Transaction. Giving back is not repaying. It is completing the circle. One completed circle today. Receive, then give back. That circle is the foundation. Not linear. Cyclical."
    },
    10: {
        "sanskrit": "दक्षिणा वै यज्ञस्य प्रतिष्ठा । यद्दक्षिणा न दद्याद्यज्ञो विशीर्येत । तस्माद्दक्षिणा देयाः । अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्नेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदग्निं समर्धयति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रस्य वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदिन्द्रं समर्धयति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सवितुर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तत्सवितारं समर्धयति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्बृहस्पतिं समर्धयति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णोर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्विष्णुं समर्धयति ।",
        "meaning": "The sacrificial fees are the foundation of the sacrifice. If he should not give fees, the sacrifice would collapse. Therefore fees should be given. He gives a gold coin to Agni. The gold coin is the form of Agni; by the form he perfects Agni. He gives a gold coin to Indra. The gold coin is the form of Indra; by the form he perfects Indra. He gives a gold coin to Savitr. The gold coin is the form of Savitr; by the form he perfects Savitr. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati. The gold coin is the form of Brhaspati; by the form he perfects Brhaspati. He gives a gold coin to Visnu. The gold coin is the form of Visnu; by the form he perfects Visnu.",
        "example": "The foundation is not what you build on. It is what you build with. Giving back is not after. It is during. One action today that includes giving back within the action itself. Not action then giving. Action as giving. That action does not collapse. It stands because it is not taking. It is offering. Offering is the foundation. Not receiving. Offering."
    },
    11: {
        "sanskrit": "दक्षिणा वै यज्ञस्य प्रतिष्ठा । यद्दक्षिणा न दद्याद्यज्ञो विशीर्येत । तस्माद्दक्षिणा देयाः । अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्नेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदग्निं समर्धयति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रस्य वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदिन्द्रं समर्धयति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सवितुर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तत्सवितारं समर्धयति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्बृहस्पतिं समर्धयति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णोर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्विष्णुं समर्धयति ।",
        "meaning": "The sacrificial fees are the foundation of the sacrifice. If he should not give fees, the sacrifice would collapse. Therefore fees should be given. He gives a gold coin to Agni. The gold coin is the form of Agni; by the form he perfects Agni. He gives a gold coin to Indra. The gold coin is the form of Indra; by the form he perfects Indra. He gives a gold coin to Savitr. The gold coin is the form of Savitr; by the form he perfects Savitr. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati. The gold coin is the form of Brhaspati; by the form he perfects Brhaspati. He gives a gold coin to Visnu. The gold coin is the form of Visnu; by the form he perfects Visnu.",
        "example": "Perfection is not elimination. It is inclusion. One action that includes all five aspects: immediate action (Agni), sustained courage (Indra), awakening (Savitr), wisdom (Brhaspati), vision (Visnu). Not excluding any. That inclusion is the gold coin. That coin perfects because it is whole, not because it is pure. Wholeness is perfection. Not purity."
    },
    12: {
        "sanskrit": "दक्षिणा वै यज्ञस्य प्रतिष्ठा । यद्दक्षिणा न दद्याद्यज्ञो विशीर्येत । तस्माद्दक्षिणा देयाः । अग्नये रुक्मं ददाति । अग्नेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदग्निं समर्धयति । इन्द्राय रुक्मं ददाति । इन्द्रस्य वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तदिन्द्रं समर्धयति । सवित्रे रुक्मं ददाति । सवितुर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तत्सवितारं समर्धयति । बृहस्पतये रुक्मं ददाति । बृहस्पतेर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्बृहस्पतिं समर्धयति । विष्णवे रुक्मं ददाति । विष्णोर्वै रुक्मो रूपम् । रूपेणैव तद्विष्णुं समर्धयति ।",
        "meaning": "The sacrificial fees are the foundation of the sacrifice. If he should not give fees, the sacrifice would collapse. Therefore fees should be given. He gives a gold coin to Agni. The gold coin is the form of Agni; by the form he perfects Agni. He gives a gold coin to Indra. The gold coin is the form of Indra; by the form he perfects Indra. He gives a gold coin to Savitr. The gold coin is the form of Savitr; by the form he perfects Savitr. He gives a gold coin to Brhaspati. The gold coin is the form of Brhaspati; by the form he perfects Brhaspati. He gives a gold coin to Visnu. The gold coin is the form of Visnu; by the form he perfects Visnu.",
        "example": "The repetition of this verse closes the Prapathaka. The teaching is simple but must be repeated: Give back. Not after. During. One action today that is itself a giving. Not taking disguised as giving. Action as offering. That action does not collapse. It stands because it is not a transaction. It is a sacrifice. Not loss. Offering. This completes Kanda 1, Prapathaka 5."
    }
}
